00:02:30.823 --> 00:02:32.460
then we get a voltage drop,

00:02:32.460 --> 00:02:33.891
because we go from plus to minus,

00:02:33.891 --> 00:02:36.724
we get a voltage drop of minus V1,

00:02:37.776 --> 00:02:40.693
and then we get another drop of V2,

00:02:41.667 --> 00:02:43.500
minus V2, equals zero.

00:02:46.274 --> 00:02:50.383
That's our KVL equation
for this circuit over here,

00:02:50.383 --> 00:02:53.106
